  "title": "AB03 - Assurance & Audit Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Audit Assistant Manager/ Audit Manager </strong></p><p><strong>5 days / 5.5 days(Saturday half day during peak period)</strong><br />0830am - 1730pm<br />$4800 - $5500 <br />Beach Road</p><p><strong>Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Manages a portfolio of engagements which includes client acceptance, engagement planning, execution and finalization of an audit engagement. </li><li>Fully accountable for the audit engagement and ensures that the engagement progress against budget and timeline is closely monitored.</li><li>Serves to develop and maintain long-term client relationships and value-add to the audit firm by identifying new business development opportunities.</li><li>Review and provides key technical expertise to ensure the quality of audit work performed is in compliance with professional standards and requirements.</li><li> Contributes towards continuous improvement in audit methodology and process.</li><li>Assume a greater role in professional development activities such as training, staff recruitment and resource planning.</li><li>required to plan, co-ordinate and supervisor various audit assignments for review by the engagement manager or partner.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree or equivalent. </li><li>At least 4 years of working experiences as Audit Assistant Manager or Audit Manager. </li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply, please send me your resume and job applied for on WhatsApp at 8093 8699 or email me at anabel.thesupreme@gmail.com (˶ᵔ ᵕ ᵔ˶)</p><p>❄️Anabel Boon Xue Qi | Consultant Associate (R25159272) |📍The Supreme HR Advisory EA No: 14C7279</p>",
